            <note xml:id="foot.f4">The first volume of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1041.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Buckle 1857–61</ref>, which CD recorded having read early in 1858 (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 4, Appendix IV, 128: 23). CD and Hooker had met <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_708.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Henry Thomas Buckle</ref> at a dinner party (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-2222.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to J. D. Hooker, 23 February [1858]</ref>, and <ref target="./DCP-LETT-2225.xml" resp="#mjhawkins" cert="high">letter from J. D. Hooker, [25] February [1858]</ref>).</note>
